  <discussion>Nasturtium gambelii is known from southern California in Los Angeles, San Bernardino, San Luis Obispo, Santa Barbara, and Ventura counties. It is likely to be found also in undisturbed, freshwater habitats elsewhere in southern California and in Mexico and Central America. Intermediates between N. gambelii and N. officinale have been found in southern California, suggesting hybridization between them. Experimental work is needed to confirm this hypothesis.</discussion>
